1
00:00:05,200 --> 00:00:06,520
(Highlight: He's telling on Ding)
He stole my card.

2
00:00:06,520 --> 00:00:07,280
Where's my meal card?

3
00:00:07,280 --> 00:00:08,000
(Asking me?)
How would I know

4
00:00:08,000 --> 00:00:08,520
where your meal card is?

5
00:00:08,520 --> 00:00:09,160
It's with you.

6
00:00:09,160 --> 00:00:10,640
No, it's not.

7
00:00:10,640 --> 00:00:11,200
(Suspicious)
Nonsense.

8
00:00:11,280 --> 00:00:12,440
Truth Taste Set and Truth Hunan Set.

9
00:00:12,440 --> 00:00:13,560
I actually want the Truth Hunan Set,

10
00:00:13,560 --> 00:00:14,520
but I only have 200. Not enough.

11
00:00:14,520 --> 00:00:15,320
(Counting on you)
So you have to buy it.

12
00:00:15,320 --> 00:00:16,440
(Copying word for word)
Right, I also want the Truth Hunan Set.

13
00:00:16,440 --> 00:00:17,200
I also only have 200.

14
00:00:17,200 --> 00:00:17,680
So I'm short too.

15
00:00:17,680 --> 00:00:18,240
What am I supposed to pay with?

16
00:00:18,640 --> 00:00:19,600
I'll have anything.

17
00:00:19,600 --> 00:00:21,280
Just spare me a bite.

18
00:00:21,440 --> 00:00:22,280
(Loving this)
Beg me.

19
00:00:22,400 --> 00:00:23,700
(Big guy goes soft)
Please.

20
00:00:23,700 --> 00:00:24,520
Please.

21
00:00:24,780 --> 00:00:25,980
(Very much enjoying this)

22
00:00:26,280 --> 00:00:27,240
I've got enough.

23
00:00:27,240 --> 00:00:27,800
Is that enough for you?

24
00:00:27,800 --> 00:00:28,360
I'm good too.

25
00:00:28,360 --> 00:00:29,320
This is all ours.

26
00:00:29,320 --> 00:00:30,720
If you keep this up,

27
00:00:30,720 --> 00:00:31,480
the Truth Supply Station

28
00:00:31,480 --> 00:00:32,960
is going to get brutal.

29
00:00:33,320 --> 00:00:34,320
His points are with me.

30
00:00:34,440 --> 00:00:35,320
(Proud)
I scanned them for him.

31
00:00:35,320 --> 00:00:36,080
That's how it is.

32
00:00:36,080 --> 00:00:37,200
His points are with you.

33
00:00:37,200 --> 00:00:38,400
(No hesitation)
My heart is with you too.

34
00:00:38,560 --> 00:00:40,080
(No)
Stop.

35
00:00:40,080 --> 00:00:41,120
Don't do this.

36
00:00:41,840 --> 00:00:42,360
They don't want you.

37
00:00:43,160 --> 00:00:43,600
Get away.

38
00:00:43,860 --> 00:00:45,140
(Hard pass)

39
00:00:45,160 --> 00:00:46,600
Get me a Truth Happiness Set.

40
00:00:46,600 --> 00:00:48,280
Two freeloaders.

41
00:00:48,280 --> 00:00:49,800
Those two are straight-up mooching.

42
00:00:49,860 --> 00:00:51,420
(Mooching together)

43
00:00:51,500 --> 00:00:52,400
(Food has arrived)

44
00:00:52,400 --> 00:00:53,640
This is great!

45
00:00:53,640 --> 00:00:55,000
(Instant noodles' No. 1 fan)
Instant noodles!

46
00:00:55,000 --> 00:00:55,920
Guys!

47
00:00:55,940 --> 00:00:56,940
(Takes a bite)

48
00:00:57,180 --> 00:00:58,260
(Want some?)

49
00:00:58,260 --> 00:00:59,400
(Crunch)

50
00:00:59,400 --> 00:01:00,480
This smells good.

51
00:01:01,160 --> 00:01:01,600
Chief investigator,

52
00:01:01,600 --> 00:01:03,520
I'm pretty sure those two are...

53
00:01:03,520 --> 00:01:04,040
What?

54
00:01:04,040 --> 00:01:04,640
The bad guys.

55
00:01:04,640 --> 00:01:05,900
(Already knew)
They've always been like this.

56
00:01:07,900 --> 00:01:11,020
=Truth Supply Station=

57
00:01:11,020 --> 00:01:11,960
(First half done)
(Time to recharge at the Supply Station)

58
00:01:11,960 --> 00:01:14,960
Truth Supply Station, here we come!

59
00:01:17,320 --> 00:01:19,720
(Regret)
If only I'd saved room for this.

60
00:01:20,040 --> 00:01:21,400
(Minutes ago)
These buns are so good.

61
00:01:22,060 --> 00:01:22,900
(That's not what you said earlier)

62
00:01:23,080 --> 00:01:24,720
(Carb lover)
I love a good plain bun.

63
00:01:24,720 --> 00:01:26,480
(The Truth S3 Ep.8 Tui City Lunch Table)
Just munching on a big bun.

64
00:01:26,480 --> 00:01:28,000
Big buns are the best. Wanna try?

65
00:01:28,000 --> 00:01:28,440
Really?

66
00:01:28,440 --> 00:01:29,560
What's wrong with buns?

67
00:01:29,560 --> 00:01:31,360
If you fill up on those, you won't
have room for the good stuff.

68
00:01:32,760 --> 00:01:34,000
Carbs are way too filling.

69
00:01:34,000 --> 00:01:34,640
Exactly.

70
00:01:34,740 --> 00:01:36,020
(Stomach capacity: critical)

71
00:01:36,040 --> 00:01:37,920
Truth Supply Station.

72
00:01:38,480 --> 00:01:42,160
During the game, players
can look out for...

73
00:01:42,160 --> 00:01:43,800
(Truth Supply Station)
Right, like the ones we just saw.

74
00:01:43,800 --> 00:01:45,240
(Stamina markers hidden around)
Stamina markers hidden around the place.

75
00:01:45,240 --> 00:01:46,160
(Tap your stamina badge to a marker)
Find one and tap your badge to it

76
00:01:46,160 --> 00:01:48,720
(Claim 100 stamina points)
to collect it right away.

77
00:01:48,720 --> 00:01:50,440
Eight stamina markers
were triggered in this dungeon.

78
00:01:50,440 --> 00:01:51,560
Unclaimed markers.

79
00:01:51,560 --> 00:01:54,640
Inside the cabinet by the
staff break room door,

80
00:01:54,640 --> 00:01:57,200
and on the shelf above the desk

81
00:01:57,200 --> 00:01:58,160
in the staff break room.

82
00:01:59,840 --> 00:02:01,480
We missed two.

83
00:02:01,480 --> 00:02:03,640
Let's see everyone's stamina points.

84
00:02:04,040 --> 00:02:05,480
Who got the most?

85
00:02:05,480 --> 00:02:07,120
Ding probably has the most right now.

86
00:02:07,120 --> 00:02:08,440
(Dungeon one Supply Station stamina tally
Ning: 200 pts, Ding: 300 pts)

87
00:02:08,460 --> 00:02:09,100
(Jin, He, Ke: 0 pts)

88
00:02:09,100 --> 00:02:11,370
(Dungeon two Supply Station stamina tally
Ning, He, Ke: 0 pts)

89
00:02:11,370 --> 00:02:12,780
(Jin: 200 pts, Ding: 600 pts)

90
00:02:12,780 --> 00:02:14,260
(Jin earned 200 stamina points)

91
00:02:14,360 --> 00:02:15,760
(#Jin scours the entire place)
Where would you hide the murder weapon?

92
00:02:15,760 --> 00:02:17,480
(Deep in detective mode)
I'd definitely put it somewhere high up.

93
00:02:17,480 --> 00:02:17,880
High?

94
00:02:17,880 --> 00:02:18,440
(Searching carefully)
Exactly.

95
00:02:18,440 --> 00:02:19,360
Where exactly?

96
00:02:19,360 --> 00:02:20,600
Have a look for us.

97
00:02:20,600 --> 00:02:21,720
Oh yes!

98
00:02:22,520 --> 00:02:23,840
(Jin +100 stamina pts)
Nice, got one!

99
00:02:26,420 --> 00:02:27,380
(Hidden stamina marker)

100
00:02:27,740 --> 00:02:28,440
(Dashes over)

101
00:02:28,440 --> 00:02:29,600
Can you get that for me?

102
00:02:29,960 --> 00:02:31,280
Would you mind getting it for me?

103
00:02:32,620 --> 00:02:34,220
(Passes it to her)

104
00:02:35,000 --> 00:02:35,800
(Jin +100 stamina pts)
Yes!

105
00:02:36,160 --> 00:02:37,160
(Ding: 600 stamina pts)
How do I have so many?

106
00:02:38,660 --> 00:02:40,020
(Quietly proud)

107
00:02:40,040 --> 00:02:42,160
(#Ding focused, searching hard)
At least you were braver today

108
00:02:42,160 --> 00:02:44,480
than Ms. Qian was.

109
00:02:44,760 --> 00:02:46,000
I'm plenty brave.

110
00:02:46,380 --> 00:02:46,980
(Double-checking)

111
00:02:50,020 --> 00:02:51,300
(Sneaky)

112
00:02:51,340 --> 00:02:53,060
(Checking again)

113
00:02:53,360 --> 00:02:54,160
Fast.

114
00:02:54,380 --> 00:02:55,340
(Ding +100 stamina pts)

115
00:02:57,420 --> 00:02:58,820
(He spots a hidden marker)

116
00:02:58,860 --> 00:03:00,220
(Ding clocks it)

117
00:03:06,260 --> 00:03:06,780
(Block)

118
00:03:06,820 --> 00:03:07,380
(Block again)

119
00:03:10,360 --> 00:03:11,720
Why is your meal card so tiny?

120
00:03:11,720 --> 00:03:12,760
How do you have a key?

121
00:03:13,120 --> 00:03:14,200
(Master of self-delusion)
This is my workstation.

122
00:03:14,200 --> 00:03:14,660
(Ding +100 stamina pts)

123
00:03:15,160 --> 00:03:17,000
He, you don't even have your meal card.

124
00:03:17,000 --> 00:03:18,280
That's not a meal card.

125
00:03:18,280 --> 00:03:19,480
What are you scanning over there?

126
00:03:19,480 --> 00:03:20,960
I forgot my meal card!

127
00:03:20,960 --> 00:03:23,360
That's a bit much, using that thing.

128
00:03:23,360 --> 00:03:25,200
(Laughing to himself)
What is he even scanning?

129
00:03:25,200 --> 00:03:26,120
I'm so annoyed.

130
00:03:26,260 --> 00:03:27,220
(Where did He's meal card go?)

131
00:03:27,420 --> 00:03:28,880
(#The mystery of He's missing meal card)

132
00:03:28,880 --> 00:03:30,280
Let me grab that.

133
00:03:30,760 --> 00:03:31,700
(He's abandoned meal card)
It's fine.

134
00:03:31,740 --> 00:03:32,780
(Perpetually forgotten)

135
00:03:34,240 --> 00:03:35,200
Come here.

136
00:03:35,200 --> 00:03:36,080
Okay.

137
00:03:36,080 --> 00:03:37,000
Can't reach it, oh well.

138
00:03:37,020 --> 00:03:38,540
(Zhang Linghe's forgotten meal card)

139
00:03:40,260 --> 00:03:41,660
(Game begins)

140
00:03:41,660 --> 00:03:42,620
(After filming wrapped)

141
00:03:42,620 --> 00:03:43,940
(Your meal card's been found)

142
00:03:43,940 --> 00:03:45,980
(Not mine. It's Linghe's)

143
00:03:45,980 --> 00:03:47,420
(Then where's yours?)

144
00:03:47,420 --> 00:03:48,100
(No idea)

145
00:03:48,100 --> 00:03:49,260
(Ke's meal card also went missing?)

146
00:03:49,480 --> 00:03:50,320
(Sad: lost my meal card)
I lost mine.

147
00:03:50,320 --> 00:03:51,260
(#The tale of Ke's
lost-and-found meal card)

148
00:03:51,260 --> 00:03:52,820
(Why does Ding have Ke's meal card?)

149
00:03:53,780 --> 00:03:55,620
(Ding's crew finds
Zhou Keyu's lost meal card)

150
00:03:56,760 --> 00:03:57,160
What's this?

151
00:03:57,160 --> 00:03:58,000
Zhou Keyu's meal card.

152
00:03:59,880 --> 00:04:01,640
Please me.

153
00:04:01,640 --> 00:04:03,640
(Being cute always works)
Ding, please.

154
00:04:04,920 --> 00:04:05,840
What's this?

155
00:04:05,840 --> 00:04:06,760
(Acting like a motorbike)
Just take it.

156
00:04:06,780 --> 00:04:08,620
(Actually looking for clues)

157
00:04:08,620 --> 00:04:10,900
(#Ding focused, searching hard)

158
00:04:10,920 --> 00:04:11,720
Hold on!

159
00:04:11,720 --> 00:04:12,520
There's a key here.

160
00:04:14,040 --> 00:04:15,040
A key!

161
00:04:15,040 --> 00:04:16,360
(Ding +100 stamina pts)
And another... Ding!

162
00:04:19,510 --> 00:04:20,830
Spilled again.

163
00:04:20,900 --> 00:04:22,420
(No idea how it happened)

164
00:04:23,500 --> 00:04:24,260
(Spots a hidden marker)

165
00:04:24,920 --> 00:04:25,940
(Tag-team mode activated)
Ding! Come here!

166
00:04:25,940 --> 00:04:27,100
(Can't wait)

167
00:04:27,820 --> 00:04:28,660
(Show yourself, stamina marker)

168
00:04:28,660 --> 00:04:29,300
(Ding +100 stamina pts)

169
00:04:30,120 --> 00:04:31,720
How did you spill it again?

170
00:04:31,720 --> 00:04:32,960
(Spilled Cup)
I spilled it.

171
00:04:32,960 --> 00:04:33,840
Bro.

172
00:04:36,520 --> 00:04:37,720
(Hidden stamina marker)
There's one here too.

173
00:04:38,900 --> 00:04:40,200
(Ding +100 stamina pts)
How are there so many?

174
00:04:42,160 --> 00:04:43,360
Ding Pudding.

175
00:04:44,320 --> 00:04:44,920
Ding.

176
00:04:45,380 --> 00:04:46,700
(Hidden stamina marker)

177
00:04:47,520 --> 00:04:48,560
I love you so much.

178
00:04:48,940 --> 00:04:49,740
(Ding +100 stamina pts)

179
00:04:50,840 --> 00:04:52,040
What's that about?

180
00:04:52,040 --> 00:04:52,840
What?

181
00:04:52,840 --> 00:04:53,360
We're partners.

182
00:04:53,360 --> 00:04:54,000
We're brothers.

183
00:04:54,060 --> 00:04:55,380
(Bros at heart)

184
00:04:55,440 --> 00:04:56,840
It's fine. I'll take it easy today.

185
00:04:56,840 --> 00:04:57,480
I won't scan anymore.

186
00:04:57,480 --> 00:04:59,120
Either way, today we'll

187
00:04:59,120 --> 00:05:00,520
just guilt-trip those two into paying.

188
00:05:00,520 --> 00:05:01,320
Deal.

189
00:05:01,320 --> 00:05:02,240
Just make them treat us.

190
00:05:02,760 --> 00:05:04,040
You're the one who scanned all of them.

191
00:05:04,100 --> 00:05:05,700
(Effortlessly played)

192
00:05:05,740 --> 00:05:06,580
(Dungeon two Supply
Station stamina tally)

193
00:05:06,580 --> 00:05:07,880
(Ning, Jin: 200 pts,  Ding: 900 pts)

194
00:05:07,880 --> 00:05:08,460
(He, Ke: 0 pts)

195
00:05:08,720 --> 00:05:10,160
(He, Ke: 0 pts)
You two got nothing.

196
00:05:10,160 --> 00:05:11,640
I scanned a lot for him.

197
00:05:11,640 --> 00:05:12,680
(Best bro)
It's all with me.

198
00:05:12,680 --> 00:05:14,120
Why did you scan for him?

199
00:05:14,480 --> 00:05:16,120
(He tells on Ke)
He stole my card.

200
00:05:16,120 --> 00:05:17,320
Where's my meal card?

201
00:05:17,320 --> 00:05:18,840
(Confident with zero ground)
How would I know where your meal card is?

202
00:05:19,520 --> 00:05:20,440
It's with you.

203
00:05:20,440 --> 00:05:21,840
No, it's not.

204
00:05:21,840 --> 00:05:22,960
(Suspicious)
Nonsense.

205
00:05:22,960 --> 00:05:24,440
How could I possibly have it?

206
00:05:24,440 --> 00:05:25,660
(Watching)

207
00:05:25,720 --> 00:05:27,040
(Sees right through him)
Your eyes dart around when you lie.

208
00:05:27,040 --> 00:05:28,040
How is this stealing?

209
00:05:28,040 --> 00:05:29,520
What do you mean I stole it?

210
00:05:30,080 --> 00:05:32,280
(He's meal card)
I picked it up for you, okay?

211
00:05:32,280 --> 00:05:33,640
Then why didn't you give it back?

212
00:05:33,640 --> 00:05:35,280
(Since the points are at zero anyway)
I'm giving it back now.

213
00:05:35,280 --> 00:05:37,700
(Sees through it all but says nothing)

214
00:05:38,120 --> 00:05:38,680
Menu.

215
00:05:39,400 --> 00:05:40,760
(Today's menu)
What's the Truth Comfort?

216
00:05:40,760 --> 00:05:42,160
Truth Comfort Set.

217
00:05:42,160 --> 00:05:43,920
We tried the Snack Boost last time.

218
00:05:43,920 --> 00:05:44,840
It's probably a lunch box again.

219
00:05:45,280 --> 00:05:46,400
Probably a lunch box.

220
00:05:46,400 --> 00:05:47,760
What's the Truth Taste Set?

221
00:05:47,760 --> 00:05:48,320
Stewed food?

222
00:05:49,120 --> 00:05:50,240
Maybe braised dishes.

223
00:05:51,120 --> 00:05:52,000
(It clicks)
Braised dishes, maybe!

224
00:05:52,640 --> 00:05:53,900
I really want the Truth Taste Set.

225
00:05:53,900 --> 00:05:54,820
(You get what I'm saying, right?)

226
00:05:54,820 --> 00:05:56,740
(Corner of mouth)

227
00:05:56,880 --> 00:05:58,840
I have a feeling the Truth Taste
Set and Truth Hunan Set

228
00:05:58,840 --> 00:06:00,080
(Eyes already set)
are going to be incredible.

229
00:06:00,520 --> 00:06:02,480
(Fellow foodies)
Hunan Set's gonna be good.

230
00:06:02,480 --> 00:06:03,640
Truth Taste Set and Truth Hunan Set.

231
00:06:03,640 --> 00:06:04,760
I actually want the Truth Hunan Set,

232
00:06:04,760 --> 00:06:05,720
but I only have 200. Not enough.

233
00:06:05,720 --> 00:06:06,520
(Counting on you)
So you have to buy it.

234
00:06:06,520 --> 00:06:07,640
(Copying word for word)
Right, I also want the Truth Hunan Set.

235
00:06:07,640 --> 00:06:08,400
I also only have 200.

236
00:06:08,400 --> 00:06:08,880
So I'm short too.

237
00:06:08,880 --> 00:06:09,440
What am I supposed to pay with?

238
00:06:09,580 --> 00:06:10,980
(Watching their little comedy show)

239
00:06:11,020 --> 00:06:12,740
(This clever pair)

240
00:06:13,080 --> 00:06:14,040
I'll have anything.

241
00:06:14,040 --> 00:06:15,760
Just spare me a bite.

242
00:06:17,960 --> 00:06:18,880
Ding, don't listen to them.

243
00:06:18,880 --> 00:06:20,080
(Tugging at bro)
Just treat me. That's enough.

244
00:06:20,080 --> 00:06:21,440
Just for the two of us to eat.

245
00:06:21,440 --> 00:06:22,440
Right, just the two of us.

246
00:06:22,500 --> 00:06:23,300
(Real ones)

247
00:06:24,560 --> 00:06:26,160
Commander!

248
00:06:26,160 --> 00:06:27,960
(Testing true friendship)
Is this where our friendship ends?

249
00:06:27,960 --> 00:06:28,560
Be honest.

250
00:06:29,720 --> 00:06:30,560
(Loving this)
Beg me.

251
00:06:31,040 --> 00:06:33,160
(Big guy goes soft)
Please.

252
00:06:33,460 --> 00:06:34,940
(Very much enjoying this)

253
00:06:34,960 --> 00:06:36,720
Help me!

254
00:06:37,440 --> 00:06:37,840
Please!

255
00:06:38,400 --> 00:06:38,760
Help me!

256
00:06:39,360 --> 00:06:40,040
(Big bro's got you)
Eat up.

257
00:06:40,040 --> 00:06:40,560
Eat what?

258
00:06:41,080 --> 00:06:41,440
Eat!

259
00:06:41,700 --> 00:06:42,940
(Life's good when someone spoils you)

260
00:06:44,520 --> 00:06:45,680
Definitely getting a Truth Hunan Set.

261
00:06:45,680 --> 00:06:47,520
It's 400 so it must be the most filling.

262
00:06:48,440 --> 00:06:50,200
You two can split a Truth Hunan Set.

263
00:06:50,200 --> 00:06:51,600
(Hard pass)
I'm not splitting with him.

264
00:06:51,600 --> 00:06:52,640
We don't get along.

265
00:06:52,640 --> 00:06:54,080
(Scheme backfired)
We're rivals. We're enemies.

266
00:06:54,080 --> 00:06:55,240
Can't be seen together.
We're competitors.

267
00:06:55,240 --> 00:06:56,900
(His little scheme is crystal clear)

268
00:06:58,960 --> 00:07:00,400
Here is what Ding has.

269
00:07:01,220 --> 00:07:02,660
(Napping. Do not disturb)

270
00:07:02,760 --> 00:07:05,120
Guys, he's got 900.

271
00:07:05,120 --> 00:07:06,760
You have 900?

272
00:07:07,240 --> 00:07:08,400
Ding's asleep.

273
00:07:08,560 --> 00:07:09,600
No, here's the thing, Ding.

274
00:07:09,620 --> 00:07:11,160
(Let's hear this)

275
00:07:11,160 --> 00:07:13,200
It resets every episode.

276
00:07:13,200 --> 00:07:14,160
So this episode,

277
00:07:14,160 --> 00:07:15,920
stockpiling is pointless. You get it?

278
00:07:15,920 --> 00:07:17,360
Right, no point hoarding.

279
00:07:17,360 --> 00:07:18,200
But if you spend it now,

280
00:07:18,200 --> 00:07:20,080
you'll earn the
respect of everyone here.

281
00:07:20,920 --> 00:07:22,040
It resets every episode?

282
00:07:22,040 --> 00:07:22,600
Yes.

283
00:07:22,600 --> 00:07:23,720
You think I don't know that?

284
00:07:24,240 --> 00:07:25,880
(Straight-faced)
We both had 100 before.

285
00:07:25,880 --> 00:07:27,120
(Really?)
I didn't spend mine last time.

286
00:07:27,120 --> 00:07:27,400
Right.

287
00:07:27,400 --> 00:07:27,980
(Everyone ganging up)
It reset.

288
00:07:28,680 --> 00:07:29,280
Both of them wiped out.

289
00:07:29,640 --> 00:07:30,560
(Teaming up)
Totally reset.

290
00:07:30,780 --> 00:07:31,580
(I'm young, don't con me)

291
00:07:32,160 --> 00:07:32,960
(He's take?)
Don't listen to them.

292
00:07:32,960 --> 00:07:35,480
(Locked-in alliance)
We triggered eight and you have 900.

293
00:07:35,680 --> 00:07:36,280
(It clicks)
Oh right.

294
00:07:36,740 --> 00:07:38,100
(Totally confused now)

295
00:07:38,140 --> 00:07:40,300
(Let's see you explain this)

296
00:07:40,440 --> 00:07:41,560
(Scrambling)
Well then, you just scanned nine times.

297
00:07:41,560 --> 00:07:42,040
Obviously.

298
00:07:42,620 --> 00:07:44,380
(Like I'd believe that)

299
00:07:44,540 --> 00:07:46,220
(Can't keep the story going)

300
00:07:46,240 --> 00:07:48,160
Ding, stick to your guns.

301
00:07:48,360 --> 00:07:50,240
Alright, I'll buy one Truth Hunan Set.

302
00:07:50,240 --> 00:07:51,920
(Today's order: Truth Hunan Set x 1)
Great, let's start with Truth Hunan Set.

303
00:07:52,280 --> 00:07:52,600
No!

304
00:07:52,600 --> 00:07:54,360
One Truth Hunan Set for this table.

305
00:07:55,400 --> 00:07:56,280
(Has a plan)
Then I'll just move over there.

306
00:07:56,800 --> 00:07:58,120
Pull the table a little closer.

307
00:08:00,440 --> 00:08:01,760
(Helpful)
Clear this out.

308
00:08:03,180 --> 00:08:04,140
(Food has arrived)

309
00:08:04,160 --> 00:08:05,480
Over here.

310
00:08:05,480 --> 00:08:07,120
Wait, this is it for 400?

311
00:08:07,680 --> 00:08:08,560
That's 400?

312
00:08:08,560 --> 00:08:09,640
This is all ours.

313
00:08:09,640 --> 00:08:10,440
(Hungry tummy)
It's really not enough.

314
00:08:11,200 --> 00:08:12,160
I've got enough.

315
00:08:12,160 --> 00:08:12,720
Is that enough for you?

316
00:08:12,720 --> 00:08:13,200
I'm good too.

317
00:08:13,680 --> 00:08:15,280
If you keep this up,

318
00:08:15,280 --> 00:08:16,400
the Truth Supply Station

319
00:08:16,400 --> 00:08:17,880
is going to get brutal.

320
00:08:22,640 --> 00:08:23,480
Where's my plate?

321
00:08:24,720 --> 00:08:25,280
(Confiscated)
Taken.

322
00:08:25,880 --> 00:08:27,560
You're eating our food
and you took the plate?

323
00:08:27,920 --> 00:08:30,000
(Not my fault!)
Didn't you just say to clear the plates?

324
00:08:30,000 --> 00:08:30,800
So I cleared them.

325
00:08:30,800 --> 00:08:32,320
You handed me the plate yourself.

326
00:08:33,320 --> 00:08:35,520
(Shameless mode on)
Ding, get your sister a Truth Taste Set.

327
00:08:36,910 --> 00:08:37,640
Okay,

328
00:08:37,640 --> 00:08:39,360
here's what I'm thinking.

329
00:08:39,360 --> 00:08:40,670
Bro can order another set,

330
00:08:40,670 --> 00:08:41,760
but we split it.

331
00:08:42,280 --> 00:08:43,480
I agree. Split it.

332
00:08:43,480 --> 00:08:44,360
Split what?

333
00:08:44,360 --> 00:08:45,360
The Truth Happiness Set.

334
00:08:45,360 --> 00:08:46,600
I put in 100, you two put in 200.

335
00:08:47,080 --> 00:08:47,440
Yes.

336
00:08:48,040 --> 00:08:49,200
I'll put in 100.

337
00:08:49,200 --> 00:08:51,360
You two don't have anything to split.

338
00:08:51,360 --> 00:08:52,320
What are you doing over there?

339
00:08:52,340 --> 00:08:54,740
(The world's top hype squad)

340
00:08:55,120 --> 00:08:56,120
His points are with me.

341
00:08:56,640 --> 00:08:57,640
(Proud)
I scanned them for him.

342
00:08:57,640 --> 00:08:58,760
That's how it is.

343
00:08:58,760 --> 00:08:59,880
His points are with you.

344
00:08:59,880 --> 00:09:02,020
(No hesitation)
My heart is with you too.

345
00:09:02,760 --> 00:09:04,280
(No, thank you)
Stop.

346
00:09:04,280 --> 00:09:05,320
Don't do this.

347
00:09:06,320 --> 00:09:06,840
They don't want you.

348
00:09:07,640 --> 00:09:08,080
Get away.

349
00:09:08,760 --> 00:09:09,240
Get away.

350
00:09:09,500 --> 00:09:11,020
(Hard pass)

351
00:09:11,040 --> 00:09:11,880
Get me a Truth Happiness Set.

352
00:09:11,880 --> 00:09:12,720
We three can share.

353
00:09:12,720 --> 00:09:14,280
Sure, split one Truth Happiness Set.

354
00:09:14,280 --> 00:09:15,720
(Today's order: Truth Happiness Set x 1)
Get us a Truth Happiness Set.

355
00:09:15,720 --> 00:09:17,400
Two freeloaders, honestly.

356
00:09:17,420 --> 00:09:19,020
(Mooching together)

357
00:09:19,060 --> 00:09:19,940
(Truth Happiness Set arrives)

358
00:09:22,240 --> 00:09:23,440
This is great!

359
00:09:25,360 --> 00:09:26,760
(Instant noodles' No. 1 fan)
Instant noodles!

360
00:09:26,760 --> 00:09:27,680
Guys!

361
00:09:27,740 --> 00:09:28,980
(Takes a bite)

362
00:09:29,280 --> 00:09:30,360
This smells good.

363
00:09:31,760 --> 00:09:33,440
What's the Truth Taste Set? Stewed food?

364
00:09:33,440 --> 00:09:34,600
Maybe braised dishes.

365
00:09:34,600 --> 00:09:36,240
I really want the Truth Taste Set.

366
00:09:36,680 --> 00:09:38,000
I want the Truth Taste Set.

367
00:09:38,280 --> 00:09:39,200
Call me bro first.

368
00:09:40,760 --> 00:09:42,160
That's nothing.

369
00:09:42,160 --> 00:09:43,240
Super easy.

370
00:09:43,240 --> 00:09:44,520
Bro.

371
00:09:44,520 --> 00:09:45,360
Big Bro Ding.

372
00:09:45,380 --> 00:09:47,220
(Trying hard not to laugh)

373
00:09:47,560 --> 00:09:49,000
Big Bro Ding is cracking.

374
00:09:49,360 --> 00:09:50,720
Ding can't hold it together.

375
00:09:50,720 --> 00:09:52,040
Quick, let's all act cute at Ding.

376
00:09:52,640 --> 00:09:54,760
Big Bro Ding!

377
00:09:54,760 --> 00:09:56,040
Get us the Truth Taste Set.

378
00:09:58,860 --> 00:10:00,660
(Pretty please)

379
00:10:01,040 --> 00:10:02,800
You two get a Truth Taste Set,

380
00:10:02,800 --> 00:10:03,640
and I'll get a Truth Comfort Set.

381
00:10:03,960 --> 00:10:05,480
(How did I get dragged into this)
No, just getting one more is fine.

382
00:10:05,480 --> 00:10:06,960
You each have 100 left.

383
00:10:07,120 --> 00:10:09,000
We need to keep ours for drinks.

384
00:10:09,000 --> 00:10:10,320
Then you two buy the drinks.

385
00:10:10,320 --> 00:10:11,320
Sure, of course, no problem.

386
00:10:11,320 --> 00:10:12,960
(The cuteness works)
Okay, I'll get the Truth Taste Set.

387
00:10:13,120 --> 00:10:14,320
(Today's order: Truth Taste Set x 1)
Add a Truth Taste Set.

388
00:10:14,320 --> 00:10:16,120
(Too funny)
Those two are straight-up mooching.

389
00:10:16,180 --> 00:10:17,500
(Eating happily)

390
00:10:17,960 --> 00:10:19,080
Want some instant noodles?

391
00:10:19,320 --> 00:10:20,400
Yeah, pass some over.

392
00:10:21,400 --> 00:10:22,880
These instant noodles are so spicy.

393
00:10:23,040 --> 00:10:24,080
So hot!

394
00:10:24,200 --> 00:10:25,560
Where are the drinks you two ordered?

395
00:10:25,840 --> 00:10:26,880
(You remember?)
What are you guys having?

396
00:10:26,880 --> 00:10:28,080
(Today's Menu)

397
00:10:28,080 --> 00:10:29,080
Just get one of everything.

398
00:10:29,560 --> 00:10:30,640
One of each?

399
00:10:30,640 --> 00:10:31,040
Yep.

400
00:10:31,520 --> 00:10:33,680
(Greedy boy ordering everything)
The water should taste good.

401
00:10:33,680 --> 00:10:35,440
We can just turn on that tap
to sort it out.

402
00:10:35,440 --> 00:10:36,600
(Just make do)
I'll grab a bowl to catch it for you.

403
00:10:37,000 --> 00:10:38,480
Remember how these two are acting now.

404
00:10:38,480 --> 00:10:40,400
They weren't like this
when they were begging me.

405
00:10:40,640 --> 00:10:41,200
Bro.

406
00:10:41,200 --> 00:10:41,640
Ding.

407
00:10:42,780 --> 00:10:43,900
(Truth Taste entering the room)

408
00:10:43,920 --> 00:10:44,480
Hot pot.

409
00:10:46,600 --> 00:10:49,120
Man, we gotta eat this.

410
00:10:49,600 --> 00:10:51,000
Sukiyaki.

411
00:10:53,380 --> 00:10:55,140
(Crunchy)

412
00:10:58,300 --> 00:10:59,980
(Have a bite)

413
00:11:05,060 --> 00:11:06,940
(Focusing on the food)

414
00:11:12,300 --> 00:11:14,100
(Eating with passion)

415
00:11:16,260 --> 00:11:18,220
(I'm gonna eat back
everything that's mine)

416
00:11:21,100 --> 00:11:22,780
(Mind-blowing flavor)

417
00:11:24,240 --> 00:11:25,880
(Unforgettable)
Honestly, Ning is a great cook.

418
00:11:26,280 --> 00:11:26,720
(Agree +1)
Yeah.

419
00:11:26,720 --> 00:11:28,520
("The Truth (Season 3)" Sneak Peek)

420
00:11:28,520 --> 00:11:30,200
This chicken soup is so savory.

421
00:11:30,200 --> 00:11:31,520
It's really good, this chicken soup.

422
00:11:32,640 --> 00:11:33,320
You can cook?

423
00:11:33,720 --> 00:11:35,720
Before getting into this industry,
I trained as a chef.

424
00:11:35,780 --> 00:11:37,120
(Totally impressed)

425
00:11:37,120 --> 00:11:39,280
What was that soup
you made before? Lamb?

426
00:11:39,760 --> 00:11:40,560
Lamb soup.

427
00:11:40,560 --> 00:11:41,760
("Wow The World" EP08 Part 2)
This looks beautiful.

428
00:11:41,760 --> 00:11:43,120
How is it so flavorful?

429
00:11:43,720 --> 00:11:44,920
Did you make it here?

430
00:11:45,040 --> 00:11:46,480
On our other show.

431
00:11:47,160 --> 00:11:48,240
By the way, this one time.

432
00:11:48,240 --> 00:11:49,920
was there a killer
in that escape room episode?

433
00:11:49,920 --> 00:11:50,320
Yeah.

434
00:11:50,640 --> 00:11:51,920
Escape room?

435
00:11:51,920 --> 00:11:53,480
The one where we had to climb up.

436
00:11:53,480 --> 00:11:55,840
The one where the water
was slowly rising.

437
00:11:56,320 --> 00:11:57,360
Yeah.

438
00:11:57,680 --> 00:11:58,880
(It was me)
I was the killer.

439
00:11:58,880 --> 00:12:00,720
Wasn't that the episode
where we opened our eyes?

440
00:12:00,820 --> 00:12:01,480
(Same memory)

441
00:12:01,480 --> 00:12:03,400
The fake killer opening eyes,

442
00:12:03,400 --> 00:12:04,160
and then Ba opened her eyes.

443
00:12:04,160 --> 00:12:04,760
Wasn't it that time?

444
00:12:05,440 --> 00:12:07,400
(Limited-edition boss)
I was the boss running that place.

445
00:12:07,400 --> 00:12:08,920
Wasn't there one time you "died"?

446
00:12:08,920 --> 00:12:10,760
Yeah, it was the episode.

447
00:12:10,760 --> 00:12:12,320
I was the boss
in that mafia game episode,

448
00:12:12,320 --> 00:12:13,440
but I wasn't the killer.

449
00:12:13,440 --> 00:12:15,720
Do you guys ever
have episodes without a killer?

450
00:12:15,720 --> 00:12:16,480
No.

451
00:12:16,480 --> 00:12:18,200
We've never had one without a killer.

452
00:12:18,440 --> 00:12:19,640
(No killer, case on pause)
Then what would we even be doing?

453
00:12:20,340 --> 00:12:21,340
(Makes sense)

454
00:12:21,600 --> 00:12:22,920
The outsider is the killer.

455
00:12:22,920 --> 00:12:24,440
Back in season one,

456
00:12:24,440 --> 00:12:26,720
it was impossible
for one of our own to be the killer.

457
00:12:26,720 --> 00:12:28,000
(Not necessarily)
So we were united against the outside.

458
00:12:28,380 --> 00:12:29,580
(I see)

459
00:12:29,880 --> 00:12:31,880
If the killer is an outsider,
it must be hard to guess.

460
00:12:31,880 --> 00:12:33,800
That requires a lot of NPCs.

461
00:12:33,800 --> 00:12:35,480
(All from experience)
You need at least three or four NPCs.

462
00:12:36,120 --> 00:12:37,960
And they have
to pop up pretty often, right?

463
00:12:38,280 --> 00:12:39,560
And they have to be
relevant to the story.

464
00:12:39,940 --> 00:12:41,380
(True that)

465
00:12:41,880 --> 00:12:42,920
What's this in the middle?

466
00:12:43,720 --> 00:12:44,480
Chicken?

467
00:12:44,480 --> 00:12:45,440
Where? This is tofu.

468
00:12:47,740 --> 00:12:48,820
(Delicious)

469
00:12:49,160 --> 00:12:50,600
This is really good.

470
00:12:50,600 --> 00:12:51,120
Yeah.

471
00:12:52,640 --> 00:12:53,880
So tasty.

472
00:12:53,880 --> 00:12:54,320
Did you try it?

473
00:12:54,380 --> 00:12:55,780
(Nodding along in agreement)

474
00:12:55,800 --> 00:12:56,720
There are noodles inside.

475
00:12:56,720 --> 00:12:57,080
Yep.

476
00:12:57,080 --> 00:12:58,520
(Full of praise)
This sukiyaki is amazing.

477
00:12:59,160 --> 00:13:00,560
(Shower with compliments)
These chicken wings are awesome too.

478
00:13:01,160 --> 00:13:02,240
If I knew,
I would've ordered two of these.

479
00:13:02,840 --> 00:13:03,960
Yeah.

480
00:13:03,960 --> 00:13:05,360
This is so good.

481
00:13:05,360 --> 00:13:07,040
(Truth Taste gets unanimous praise)
This is pretty healthy.

482
00:13:07,040 --> 00:13:07,840
Ding is hilarious,

483
00:13:07,840 --> 00:13:08,600
asking me to call him bro.

484
00:13:09,240 --> 00:13:11,480
We would literally call someone dad.

485
00:13:11,480 --> 00:13:12,120
That...

486
00:13:12,120 --> 00:13:13,480
Calling someone bro is nothing.

487
00:13:15,520 --> 00:13:16,920
You overestimated our self-esteem.

488
00:13:17,560 --> 00:13:18,040
Totally.

489
00:13:21,760 --> 00:13:23,560
But actually,
Bai used to hate saying it.

490
00:13:23,560 --> 00:13:24,960
No, he's fine with calling me that,

491
00:13:24,960 --> 00:13:26,440
but he'd always add a word,

492
00:13:26,440 --> 00:13:27,160
Dad.

493
00:13:27,640 --> 00:13:28,640
Dad, right.

494
00:13:28,640 --> 00:13:30,240
We have absolutely no shame.

495
00:13:30,240 --> 00:13:31,040
Yeah, none of that.

496
00:13:31,640 --> 00:13:32,160
Because as actors,

497
00:13:32,640 --> 00:13:34,640
we're all just
playing characters in this setting.

498
00:13:40,760 --> 00:13:41,720
Where are our drinks?

499
00:13:42,380 --> 00:13:43,380
(They still remember that?)

500
00:13:44,000 --> 00:13:44,860
(A sudden wake-up call)
We didn't order.

501
00:13:45,040 --> 00:13:45,760
What are you guys drinking?

502
00:13:46,720 --> 00:13:47,240
Soda.

503
00:13:47,240 --> 00:13:48,020
(He's reminder)

504
00:13:49,560 --> 00:13:50,200
Let's get some soda.

505
00:13:50,200 --> 00:13:51,640
(Sparks of generosity)
Give us two pitchers of soda.

506
00:13:51,960 --> 00:13:52,360
One is fine.

507
00:13:52,360 --> 00:13:53,000
Two.

508
00:13:53,000 --> 00:13:53,800
No, two pitchers.

509
00:13:53,800 --> 00:13:55,960
They serve it in a pitcher.
You pour it out.

510
00:13:55,960 --> 00:13:57,600
(One pitcher is not enough)
One pitcher won't even fill six cups.

511
00:13:58,520 --> 00:13:59,200
One pitcher should be enough.

512
00:14:00,520 --> 00:14:02,320
So you want to order
two pitchers of soda?

513
00:14:02,840 --> 00:14:04,000
Two sodas.

514
00:14:04,400 --> 00:14:05,920
I think one is plenty.

515
00:14:05,920 --> 00:14:06,680
Throw in a free one.

516
00:14:06,960 --> 00:14:07,960
Yeah, give us a complimentary one.

517
00:14:08,440 --> 00:14:09,580
(Top-tier business mind)
You really know how to negotiate.

518
00:14:09,700 --> 00:14:10,860
(Today's Menu: One order of soda)

519
00:14:11,280 --> 00:14:12,880
Since the players successfully

520
00:14:12,880 --> 00:14:15,920
helped Mr. Wu complete
the side quest in dungeon one,

521
00:14:16,640 --> 00:14:18,400
the system will reward you
with buy one, get five free.

522
00:14:18,400 --> 00:14:19,020
(Mission accomplished.
Glass retrieval mission)

523
00:14:19,100 --> 00:14:19,980
(Some are thrilled)

524
00:14:20,380 --> 00:14:21,140
(Others are worried)

525
00:14:21,200 --> 00:14:22,520
From this moment on,

526
00:14:23,000 --> 00:14:24,480
cracking the case
has nothing to do with me.

527
00:14:24,840 --> 00:14:25,440
Why is that?

528
00:14:25,920 --> 00:14:27,080
My only goal is to...

529
00:14:27,240 --> 00:14:27,760
Make money.

530
00:14:27,860 --> 00:14:28,320
(I totally feel you)

531
00:14:28,320 --> 00:14:29,560
I need to score these points

532
00:14:29,560 --> 00:14:31,160
so I can have the final say next time.

533
00:14:31,260 --> 00:14:32,540
(I believe in you)

534
00:14:32,580 --> 00:14:33,860
(Really?)

535
00:14:36,120 --> 00:14:37,400
Can we get a refund on the leftovers?

536
00:14:37,400 --> 00:14:38,600
Yeah, I think this dish...

537
00:14:38,600 --> 00:14:40,040
(Forming a united front)

538
00:14:40,040 --> 00:14:41,800
This dish is making
my stomach hurt a little.

539
00:14:41,800 --> 00:14:43,200
I think I need to send it back.

540
00:14:43,560 --> 00:14:44,280
(Chipping in)
I think so too.

541
00:14:45,040 --> 00:14:46,720
Eating it makes me sick.

542
00:14:47,380 --> 00:14:49,100
(Watching the drama unfold)

543
00:14:49,120 --> 00:14:50,280
Let me try it again. It's a bit...

544
00:14:52,000 --> 00:14:52,720
Is it spoiled?

545
00:14:52,800 --> 00:14:53,640
It does feel a bit bad.

546
00:14:53,880 --> 00:14:55,280
You need to give a specific reason.

547
00:14:56,000 --> 00:14:58,280
First of all, I hate celery,

548
00:14:58,280 --> 00:14:59,800
but there's a ton of it in here.

549
00:14:59,860 --> 00:15:01,460
(Saying no but eating anyway)

550
00:15:01,760 --> 00:15:03,440
Yeah, and I don't think it tastes good.

551
00:15:03,500 --> 00:15:05,300
(Actions speak louder than words)

552
00:15:05,320 --> 00:15:07,040
You didn't even ask
about our dietary restrictions.

553
00:15:07,600 --> 00:15:08,840
None of us eat celery.

554
00:15:09,200 --> 00:15:10,960
Yeah, you just served it
without checking.

555
00:15:11,600 --> 00:15:12,920
Actually, I think this one
is just mediocre too.

556
00:15:13,360 --> 00:15:14,640
Dietary restrictions
were collected beforehand.

557
00:15:14,700 --> 00:15:16,220
(Their little trick gets exposed)

558
00:15:16,400 --> 00:15:17,480
What are my restriction?

559
00:15:18,080 --> 00:15:19,000
Checking right now.

560
00:15:21,760 --> 00:15:23,160
I don't even eat rice,

561
00:15:23,680 --> 00:15:24,880
and yet he actually served me rice.

562
00:15:25,220 --> 00:15:27,420
(You're way too funny)

563
00:15:27,680 --> 00:15:29,040
When you logged into the game,

564
00:15:29,040 --> 00:15:30,560
everyone's information was collected.

565
00:15:31,120 --> 00:15:32,000
I filled it out.

566
00:15:34,320 --> 00:15:34,640
Wait, no.

567
00:15:35,240 --> 00:15:36,320
But this chili,

568
00:15:36,320 --> 00:15:37,280
there's way too much of it.

569
00:15:37,280 --> 00:15:39,140
(Switching to spice-overload mode)

570
00:15:39,280 --> 00:15:40,160
He's feeling unwell.

571
00:15:40,160 --> 00:15:40,800
(Stepping into character)

572
00:15:40,800 --> 00:15:42,240
(Keeping up)
He's burning up from the spice.

573
00:15:43,480 --> 00:15:44,160
My stomach aches.

574
00:15:44,800 --> 00:15:46,200
You guys are here
to scam the restaurant.

575
00:15:46,260 --> 00:15:47,780
(Scheme exposed)

576
00:15:47,920 --> 00:15:49,320
Give us a 400-yuan refund.

577
00:15:49,640 --> 00:15:50,120
Yeah.

578
00:15:50,640 --> 00:15:51,760
You can just refund me 100.

579
00:15:51,760 --> 00:15:52,100
(Bargaining)

580
00:15:52,180 --> 00:15:53,540
(She's so good)

581
00:15:54,500 --> 00:15:55,340
(Are you serious?)

582
00:15:57,600 --> 00:15:58,680
(Feeling the peer pressure)
People like you

583
00:15:58,680 --> 00:15:59,640
are the ones who only

584
00:15:59,640 --> 00:16:01,880
care about their own interests
in times of chaos.

585
00:16:03,920 --> 00:16:05,000
Look who's talking.

586
00:16:05,800 --> 00:16:07,040
How much did you spend yourself?

587
00:16:07,840 --> 00:16:08,480
I spent 100 too.

588
00:16:08,980 --> 00:16:10,540
(Honest Ning)

589
00:16:10,880 --> 00:16:11,640
It's better when it's warm.

590
00:16:18,640 --> 00:16:19,080
This is so good.

591
00:16:19,080 --> 00:16:19,780
(Super delicious)

592
00:16:22,040 --> 00:16:23,560
Ding, can you at least pretend a bit?

593
00:16:23,560 --> 00:16:25,240
You're saying this dish
is too spicy and tastes bad,

594
00:16:25,240 --> 00:16:26,280
yet you haven't stopped eating.

595
00:16:26,480 --> 00:16:27,160
(Critique)
Just stuffing it.

596
00:16:27,760 --> 00:16:28,920
It's way too spicy.

597
00:16:29,880 --> 00:16:30,800
But it goes well with rice.

598
00:16:30,800 --> 00:16:32,120
It's too spicy, but it's good.

599
00:16:33,360 --> 00:16:35,280
What even is this?
I can't really tell what I'm eating.

600
00:16:35,280 --> 00:16:35,920
It's pretty good.

601
00:16:36,020 --> 00:16:37,340
(Meat, Sliced beef, Beef tripe)

602
00:16:37,720 --> 00:16:38,120
Beef tripe.

603
00:16:39,120 --> 00:16:39,760
Sliced beef, I think.

604
00:16:40,720 --> 00:16:41,880
There's a bit of everything in there.

605
00:16:41,880 --> 00:16:43,120
Some tripe and stuff too.

606
00:16:43,360 --> 00:16:44,400
Is this potato?

607
00:16:44,400 --> 00:16:45,000
This is so good.

608
00:16:45,480 --> 00:16:46,080
Which one?

609
00:16:46,760 --> 00:16:48,060
(Suddenly remembering the main quest)
It's terrible.

610
00:16:48,560 --> 00:16:49,540
(Foodie mode activated)
Which one tastes good?

611
00:16:50,080 --> 00:16:50,520
This one.

612
00:16:50,780 --> 00:16:51,580
(Let me try)

613
00:16:55,800 --> 00:16:57,400
These three are actually all decent.

614
00:16:57,960 --> 00:16:58,640
Not that spicy.

615
00:16:59,520 --> 00:17:01,100
(Mouth on fire)
These instant noodles are too spicy.

616
00:17:01,140 --> 00:17:01,760
(Back to getting a refund)

617
00:17:01,760 --> 00:17:03,040
They didn't even put meat in this one.

618
00:17:04,400 --> 00:17:06,000
Yeah, why isn't there
any meat in this dish?

619
00:17:10,920 --> 00:17:12,350
Once you finish that bowl of rice,

620
00:17:12,350 --> 00:17:13,240
won't they give you more?

621
00:17:13,560 --> 00:17:15,280
It's getting hard to find things
to complain about.

622
00:17:15,740 --> 00:17:17,660
(Am I busted?)

623
00:17:18,200 --> 00:17:19,160
Ours doesn't have meat either.

624
00:17:20,310 --> 00:17:21,280
Was this supposed to have meat?

625
00:17:21,540 --> 00:17:22,820
(Learning fast)

626
00:17:22,960 --> 00:17:24,000
Nope.

627
00:17:24,000 --> 00:17:25,440
I haven't eaten a single piece.

628
00:17:25,440 --> 00:17:26,200
Let's eat a bit more.

629
00:17:26,200 --> 00:17:26,960
We don't need any noodles.

630
00:17:26,960 --> 00:17:28,520
Let's just get a bit more of everything.

631
00:17:28,520 --> 00:17:30,400
Isn't this just mushrooms?

632
00:17:30,720 --> 00:17:31,440
Take this away.

633
00:17:31,500 --> 00:17:33,340
(Director Ding guiding the scene)
Say that again.

634
00:17:35,220 --> 00:17:35,820
(#Detective team trying hard to act)

635
00:17:35,840 --> 00:17:36,560
Isn't this

636
00:17:36,560 --> 00:17:37,760
just a vegetarian dish?

637
00:17:38,080 --> 00:17:38,480
Who knows?

638
00:17:38,920 --> 00:17:39,840
A vegetarian dish?

639
00:17:40,320 --> 00:17:41,880
When I filled out the survey,

640
00:17:41,880 --> 00:17:42,920
I wrote that I must have meat.

641
00:17:43,480 --> 00:17:44,000
Me too.

642
00:17:44,720 --> 00:17:45,600
Where's the meat in this?

643
00:17:45,600 --> 00:17:47,280
I'm pretty sure
it's supposed to have meat.

644
00:17:47,280 --> 00:17:49,320
When I filled the survey,
I said I don't like veggies.

645
00:17:49,320 --> 00:17:49,960
There are so many veggies.

646
00:17:52,220 --> 00:17:54,100
(Breaking character in a split second)

647
00:17:54,120 --> 00:17:55,080
Just refund us 100.

648
00:17:55,880 --> 00:17:57,200
Refund Ning and me 100 each.

649
00:17:57,300 --> 00:17:59,460
(What about me?)

650
00:17:59,760 --> 00:18:00,360
The moment you say that,

651
00:18:00,360 --> 00:18:01,920
a pair of deeply sincere eyes
looks right over.

652
00:18:02,620 --> 00:18:04,580
(Ding is too funny)

653
00:18:04,640 --> 00:18:06,120
Player feedback received.

654
00:18:06,120 --> 00:18:09,000
Leave a good review to get
a 100 stamina points cashback.

655
00:18:09,200 --> 00:18:09,680
100...

656
00:18:12,160 --> 00:18:13,200
This is so delicious.

657
00:18:13,200 --> 00:18:14,500
(Pouring on the praise)

658
00:18:14,760 --> 00:18:15,960
It's so good I want to dance.

659
00:18:19,240 --> 00:18:20,200
Can you refund me 100?

660
00:18:20,200 --> 00:18:21,760
(Utterly confused)
Wait, he's not even the chef.

661
00:18:21,760 --> 00:18:24,240
What's the point of you
saying it tastes good?

662
00:18:25,040 --> 00:18:25,680
Praise it together.

663
00:18:26,320 --> 00:18:27,400
It's not like
they're giving me the money.

664
00:18:28,080 --> 00:18:29,280
(Who gets the cashback?)
Who does the refund go to?

665
00:18:29,920 --> 00:18:30,760
Refund it to me first.

666
00:18:31,300 --> 00:18:32,120
(I have a plan)
How about refunding it to me?

667
00:18:32,600 --> 00:18:33,200
To me first.

668
00:18:33,920 --> 00:18:34,960
(Internal competition triggered)
It has to go to me.

669
00:18:34,960 --> 00:18:35,600
I spent 700.

670
00:18:37,280 --> 00:18:38,440
What's your balance right now?

671
00:18:39,000 --> 00:18:39,400
200.

672
00:18:40,080 --> 00:18:41,280
Can't you see them

673
00:18:41,280 --> 00:18:42,400
for who they really are by now?

674
00:18:42,960 --> 00:18:43,680
(Continuing to brainwash)
You have the most.

675
00:18:44,840 --> 00:18:46,800
You two really belong here.

676
00:18:46,820 --> 00:18:48,500
(Laughing hysterically)

677
00:18:48,680 --> 00:18:49,680
No, this proves one thing.

678
00:18:49,680 --> 00:18:51,280
In any harsh environment,

679
00:18:51,280 --> 00:18:51,920
we can survive.

680
00:18:52,360 --> 00:18:53,720
(Very deep)
You gotta see through human nature.

681
00:18:53,920 --> 00:18:55,400
This 100 should be added equally.

682
00:18:56,240 --> 00:18:57,240
Otherwise, giving him 100

683
00:18:57,240 --> 00:18:58,680
is basically deducting 100
from each of us.

684
00:18:59,060 --> 00:19:00,540
(What a sharp mind)

685
00:19:02,200 --> 00:19:02,640
Am I right?

686
00:19:03,240 --> 00:19:04,000
You're way too good at math.

687
00:19:05,560 --> 00:19:06,560
What kind of logic is that?

688
00:19:06,560 --> 00:19:07,280
If he gets 100,

689
00:19:07,280 --> 00:19:08,280
it means each of us...

690
00:19:08,280 --> 00:19:09,600
Didn't get that 100.

691
00:19:09,600 --> 00:19:11,400
No, we lose 100.

692
00:19:11,400 --> 00:19:12,640
If you don't pick up money, it's a loss.

693
00:19:12,640 --> 00:19:13,400
Is that what you mean?

694
00:19:14,120 --> 00:19:14,640
Exactly.

695
00:19:16,040 --> 00:19:17,480
Quick, let's start
praising the food, come on.

696
00:19:17,920 --> 00:19:18,680
Who does the cashback go to?

697
00:19:19,160 --> 00:19:19,920
Who gets it?

698
00:19:20,480 --> 00:19:21,620
(Confidently)
To me, obviously.

699
00:19:22,280 --> 00:19:23,720
Let's get the prize money first,

700
00:19:23,720 --> 00:19:25,160
then we can talk
about splitting the loot, alright?

701
00:19:25,640 --> 00:19:27,480
I want to figure out the split first.

702
00:19:27,680 --> 00:19:28,960
How about this?
Let's do rock-paper-scissors.

703
00:19:29,760 --> 00:19:30,200
Fine.

704
00:19:30,880 --> 00:19:31,920
Let's do rock-paper-scissors.

705
00:19:32,360 --> 00:19:33,160
The winner gets the cashback.

706
00:19:33,800 --> 00:19:34,240
Okay.

707
00:19:35,000 --> 00:19:35,920
One round.

708
00:19:35,920 --> 00:19:36,280
Cool.

709
00:19:36,280 --> 00:19:36,960
Rock, paper...

710
00:19:40,080 --> 00:19:40,760
Scissors, shoot.

711
00:19:40,760 --> 00:19:41,700
(Scissors, Paper)

712
00:19:41,780 --> 00:19:43,660
(Leaving with regrets)

713
00:19:44,840 --> 00:19:45,840
I'm out of options.

714
00:19:46,360 --> 00:19:47,560
(Furious)
What even is this?

715
00:19:47,560 --> 00:19:48,400
It tastes awful.

716
00:19:49,000 --> 00:19:49,520
What a joke.

717
00:19:49,520 --> 00:19:50,640
Then I'll give it to you, okay?

718
00:19:50,640 --> 00:19:51,520
You ordered drinks for us.

719
00:19:51,600 --> 00:19:52,360
Yeah, of course.

720
00:19:53,200 --> 00:19:54,320
Put it under Ning's account.

721
00:19:54,340 --> 00:19:55,820
(What's that supposed to mean?)

722
00:19:55,840 --> 00:19:56,840
For the Truth Happiness Set,

723
00:19:56,840 --> 00:19:58,120
I'll pay 100, and you guys pay 200.

724
00:19:58,120 --> 00:19:59,960
Okay, I'll order Truth Hunan.

725
00:19:59,960 --> 00:20:01,600
Okay, I'll order Truth Taste then.

726
00:20:01,600 --> 00:20:02,840
How come they get to be the good guys?

727
00:20:05,120 --> 00:20:06,100
(Upping the praise for the reward)
No, I actually think

728
00:20:06,440 --> 00:20:08,680
this meal is incredibly hearty.

729
00:20:08,680 --> 00:20:09,920
It just has everything.

730
00:20:09,920 --> 00:20:11,240
(Deadpan)
It tastes like home to me.

731
00:20:11,240 --> 00:20:11,760
Exactly.

732
00:20:12,080 --> 00:20:13,680
Eating this stuff

733
00:20:13,680 --> 00:20:14,720
in this cafeteria today

734
00:20:14,720 --> 00:20:15,720
gives you that kind of,

735
00:20:15,720 --> 00:20:17,520
you know, childhood taste.

736
00:20:17,520 --> 00:20:17,960
Yeah,

737
00:20:17,960 --> 00:20:19,080
and it gives you so much energy

738
00:20:19,080 --> 00:20:20,280
to go and fight for justice.

739
00:20:20,840 --> 00:20:21,880
(Agreeing)
I totally agree.

740
00:20:21,880 --> 00:20:22,840
What do you think, Ding?

741
00:20:23,260 --> 00:20:24,940
(Completely heartbroken. Do not disturb)

742
00:20:24,960 --> 00:20:26,880
I think this meal is so good
to the point where

743
00:20:26,880 --> 00:20:29,160
it made me realize things
about human nature.

744
00:20:30,600 --> 00:20:30,840
Yeah.

745
00:20:30,840 --> 00:20:32,160
(Seizing the opportunity)
The goodness of human.

746
00:20:32,160 --> 00:20:33,480
Goodness of human.

747
00:20:33,480 --> 00:20:35,600
I feel like after finishing this meal,

748
00:20:35,600 --> 00:20:36,640
after eating so much delicious food,

749
00:20:36,640 --> 00:20:37,880
I can already lock in the killer.

750
00:20:38,360 --> 00:20:39,520
Everyone got smarter.

751
00:20:39,520 --> 00:20:40,680
We got smarter.

752
00:20:40,680 --> 00:20:42,000
It even boosted our IQ.

753
00:20:42,220 --> 00:20:43,140
(Watching the show)

754
00:20:43,280 --> 00:20:43,800
Yep.

755
00:20:44,560 --> 00:20:45,420
(Dissatisfied)
I feel hurt.

756
00:20:45,420 --> 00:20:46,340
(The reward should've been mine)
I feel hurt.

757
00:20:47,640 --> 00:20:48,760
(Reinterpreting it)
Because this is so delicious

758
00:20:48,760 --> 00:20:50,760
that it left a scar in his heart.

759
00:20:50,760 --> 00:20:52,320
Next time he eats this,

760
00:20:52,320 --> 00:20:53,680
he'll remember this scar all over again.

761
00:20:54,620 --> 00:20:57,220
(You can really talk your way out)

762
00:20:57,240 --> 00:20:57,680
Detective,

763
00:20:57,680 --> 00:20:59,560
I think those two are definitely...

764
00:21:00,000 --> 00:21:00,720
What?

765
00:21:00,720 --> 00:21:01,320
The bad guys.

766
00:21:01,800 --> 00:21:02,880
No.

767
00:21:02,880 --> 00:21:04,140
(Knowing them too well)
They've always been like this.

768
00:21:06,240 --> 00:21:08,800
The cashback has been deposited
into Ning Bubble's account.

769
00:21:09,380 --> 00:21:10,940
(It's all mine)

770
00:21:11,020 --> 00:21:12,580
(Envious)

771
00:21:12,840 --> 00:21:14,320
I just felt my phone vibrate.

772
00:21:14,320 --> 00:21:15,040
It's in my account.

773
00:21:15,040 --> 00:21:15,640
My phone vibrated.

774
00:21:16,120 --> 00:21:16,840
They wired the money.

775
00:21:17,300 --> 00:21:18,310
(Order: Truth Hunan Set - 400 points)

776
00:21:18,310 --> 00:21:19,310
(Truth Happiness Set - 300 points,
Truth Taste Set - 200 points)

777
00:21:19,320 --> 00:21:20,180
(Truth Soda (Buy 1 Get 5 Free)
- 20 points)

778
00:21:20,180 --> 00:21:20,970
(Dungeon Two Supply Station
Stamina Point Balance)

779
00:21:20,970 --> 00:21:21,800
(Liu Yuning: 180 points
(includes 100 cashback))

780
00:21:21,800 --> 00:21:22,660
(Jin Jing: 100 points,
Ding Chengxin: 200 points)

781
00:21:22,680 --> 00:21:23,500
(Zhang Linghe: 0 points,
Zhou Keyu: 0 points)

782
00:21:24,040 --> 00:21:25,360
This udon is actually pretty good.

783
00:21:29,920 --> 00:21:31,160
Eating the udon I ordered.

784
00:21:33,640 --> 00:21:34,320
You ordered this?

785
00:21:35,100 --> 00:21:36,460
(Of course)

786
00:21:36,720 --> 00:21:38,320
You're the one

787
00:21:38,320 --> 00:21:39,640
who lost the rock-paper-scissors.

788
00:21:40,020 --> 00:21:42,340
(Forced smile)

789
00:21:42,600 --> 00:21:43,280
He's out.

790
00:21:44,520 --> 00:21:45,120
Yeah.

791
00:21:45,800 --> 00:21:46,600
Eat some carrots.

792
00:21:47,160 --> 00:21:47,720
Cool off.

793
00:21:52,840 --> 00:21:53,920
We're proudly at zero points.

794
00:21:53,920 --> 00:21:54,720
Proudly at zero.

795
00:21:54,960 --> 00:21:55,640
You two just eat in silence.

796
00:21:56,440 --> 00:21:57,520
You two ate the most.

797
00:21:57,520 --> 00:21:59,280
(Stepping out of the spotlight)
No points, but we don't join the war.

798
00:21:59,280 --> 00:21:59,520
No.

799
00:21:59,520 --> 00:22:00,480
Actually, to survive in this society,

800
00:22:00,480 --> 00:22:01,480
you gotta find yourself a boss.

801
00:22:01,480 --> 00:22:03,720
Right now, Ding is your boss.

802
00:22:04,360 --> 00:22:05,000
Clinging to the boss now.

803
00:22:06,000 --> 00:22:06,600
Riding his coattails.

804
00:22:07,400 --> 00:22:08,960
It's like they say,
it's lonely at the top.

805
00:22:08,960 --> 00:22:09,880
We'd rather stay at the bottom.

806
00:22:09,880 --> 00:22:10,720
It's much more...

807
00:22:11,600 --> 00:22:12,320
You get to eat your fill.

808
00:22:12,660 --> 00:22:14,620
(All thanks to Ding)

809
00:22:14,760 --> 00:22:16,680
I actually think Ke's strategy
is pretty good.

810
00:22:17,120 --> 00:22:18,040
"Stealing" someone else's meal card.

811
00:22:18,620 --> 00:22:19,720
(Cracking me up)

812
00:22:19,720 --> 00:22:20,720
No, honestly.

813
00:22:21,200 --> 00:22:22,560
I really just picked it up by accident.

814
00:22:22,560 --> 00:22:23,800
(Dead serious)
I really did just find it.

815
00:22:23,800 --> 00:22:24,840
And then when it was time to buy food,

816
00:22:24,840 --> 00:22:25,680
he gave it back to me.

817
00:22:28,000 --> 00:22:29,120
Originally, for this segment,

818
00:22:29,120 --> 00:22:30,640
I just wanted to tease him a bit,

819
00:22:30,640 --> 00:22:31,520
like, using his card to pay.

820
00:22:31,520 --> 00:22:32,720
But it turned out his balance was zero.

821
00:22:33,280 --> 00:22:34,520
Both of our balances are zero?

822
00:22:34,960 --> 00:22:35,720
So I thought, forget it.

823
00:22:35,720 --> 00:22:36,760
This prank is canceled.

824
00:22:38,720 --> 00:22:40,440
Why do you think
I wasn't even looking for my card?

825
00:22:40,440 --> 00:22:42,520
Walking down the street
and finding a whole wallet,

826
00:22:43,320 --> 00:22:44,240
only to realize it's empty.

827
00:22:45,840 --> 00:22:46,680
So for this episode,

828
00:22:46,680 --> 00:22:48,760
you didn't even get to swipe it once?

829
00:22:48,760 --> 00:22:50,360
(Protecting an empty card)
He was protecting my card.

830
00:22:50,360 --> 00:22:52,280
(Still dropped his guard)
I was betting that there'd be money,

831
00:22:52,280 --> 00:22:52,800
you know?

832
00:22:52,800 --> 00:22:54,360
While trying to mess with someone,

833
00:22:54,360 --> 00:22:55,560
you ended up messing with yourself.

834
00:22:55,560 --> 00:22:56,240
Exactly.

835
00:22:56,240 --> 00:22:57,600
(Realizing it now)
Yet another profound life lesson.

836
00:22:57,600 --> 00:22:59,080
What were you doing
rooting through that cabinet?

837
00:22:59,080 --> 00:22:59,880
Is there something inside?

838
00:23:00,600 --> 00:23:00,960
Knee pads.

839
00:23:01,800 --> 00:23:02,920
(Breathe)
Breathe? What?

840
00:23:02,920 --> 00:23:03,360
Knee pads.

841
00:23:03,360 --> 00:23:04,200
(Knee pads)

842
00:23:04,200 --> 00:23:05,040
We're gonna have to crawl.

843
00:23:05,040 --> 00:23:05,560
Oh, knee pads.

844
00:23:06,240 --> 00:23:07,040
We'll be crawling later.

845
00:23:07,520 --> 00:23:08,120
(Caring)
Eat up.

846
00:23:08,760 --> 00:23:09,400
Eat less.

847
00:23:09,880 --> 00:23:10,840
Eat up.

848
00:23:10,840 --> 00:23:12,720
Otherwise, you're gonna
end up throwing up later.

849
00:23:13,200 --> 00:23:13,640
No, you won't.

850
00:23:13,640 --> 00:23:15,520
Trust me. You're gonna be
starving later tonight.

851
00:23:15,760 --> 00:23:16,800
We have to crawl until tonight?

852
00:23:17,520 --> 00:23:18,640
By the time we crawl out, it'll be dark.

853
00:23:19,120 --> 00:23:20,040
For real?

854
00:23:20,560 --> 00:23:21,420
(Trust me)
For real.

855
00:23:21,480 --> 00:23:23,040
(One dares to ask)
Did you write the script?

856
00:23:23,200 --> 00:23:23,600
Yeah.

857
00:23:23,600 --> 00:23:24,540
(One dares to answer)

858
00:23:24,640 --> 00:23:26,140
(Striking back instantly)
Jin is the killer. I wrote it.

859
00:23:27,800 --> 00:23:29,680
When Jin just mentioned
she was the killer,

860
00:23:29,680 --> 00:23:30,720
her eyes darted to the side.

861
00:23:31,720 --> 00:23:32,240
(Fierce)
What now?

862
00:23:32,840 --> 00:23:34,240
That classic look of panic.

863
00:23:34,240 --> 00:23:35,920
You're observing me so closely.

864
00:23:37,440 --> 00:23:38,960
Sitting the furthest away,

865
00:23:38,960 --> 00:23:40,200
yet paying the most attention to me.

866
00:23:41,400 --> 00:23:42,200
What about Ning then?

867
00:23:43,320 --> 00:23:44,440
Ning doesn't even dare to make a sound.

868
00:23:46,800 --> 00:23:48,120
You're totally targeting him.

869
00:23:48,600 --> 00:23:49,480
Look at him.

870
00:23:49,480 --> 00:23:50,400
(Suspected bad guy. A lifelong trauma)
It was him yesterday,

871
00:23:50,400 --> 00:23:51,560
so it's definitely him again today,

872
00:23:51,560 --> 00:23:52,240
or maybe it's you.

873
00:23:57,840 --> 00:23:58,720
Let's finish off these noodles.

874
00:23:59,320 --> 00:23:59,880
Don't waste them.

875
00:24:00,320 --> 00:24:01,360
Finish off?

876
00:24:01,840 --> 00:24:03,120
How can I finish such a huge bowl?

877
00:24:03,800 --> 00:24:04,640
It's not that much.

878
00:24:04,640 --> 00:24:05,520
That's how noodles are.

879
00:24:05,520 --> 00:24:07,240
You eat for ages,
and there's still a ton left.

880
00:24:07,680 --> 00:24:08,520
They expand.

881
00:24:08,520 --> 00:24:10,400
And it feels like the more you eat,
the more there is.

882
00:24:10,400 --> 00:24:10,880
Yeah.

883
00:24:10,880 --> 00:24:11,640
(Relatable)

884
00:24:11,640 --> 00:24:12,920
You can't handle spicy food, right?

885
00:24:12,920 --> 00:24:14,280
(I'm from Chongqing)
I can. I'm from Chongqing.

886
00:24:14,280 --> 00:24:15,600
(I'm from Jiangsu)
I can't handle spice at all.

887
00:24:15,600 --> 00:24:16,280
You're from Chongqing?

888
00:24:16,760 --> 00:24:17,080
Yep.

889
00:24:17,680 --> 00:24:18,760
(Misheard, but still asking sincerely)
You can't handle spice?

890
00:24:18,920 --> 00:24:19,920
I can.

891
00:24:19,920 --> 00:24:21,440
(Asking in all sincerity)
Is Chongqing food or Hunan food spicier?

892
00:24:21,440 --> 00:24:22,400
Jiangxi food is the spiciest.

893
00:24:22,920 --> 00:24:23,360
(I agree)
Yeah.

894
00:24:23,760 --> 00:24:24,880
Chongqing food can be spicy too,

895
00:24:24,880 --> 00:24:25,640
but it's super fragrant.

896
00:24:25,920 --> 00:24:27,040
It's a numbing sort of spicy.

897
00:24:27,040 --> 00:24:28,840
A restaurant I used to work at before

898
00:24:28,840 --> 00:24:30,640
actually served Jiangxi cuisine.

899
00:24:30,640 --> 00:24:31,800
And over there, they would basically

900
00:24:31,800 --> 00:24:33,480
(Stir-frying chilies with chilies)
stir-fry chilies with chilies.

901
00:24:33,920 --> 00:24:34,920
(Sincere once again)
What's there to eat?

902
00:24:34,920 --> 00:24:36,040
I don't mean stir-frying meat.

903
00:24:36,040 --> 00:24:37,280
They just stir-fried chilies
with chilies.

904
00:24:37,280 --> 00:24:38,120
We just ate pure chilies.

905
00:24:38,120 --> 00:24:39,680
(Sounds spicy)
The kitchen must have been hell.

906
00:24:40,600 --> 00:24:41,640
That's just how Jiangxi food is.

907
00:24:42,280 --> 00:24:43,520
Zhou Keyu, where are you from?

908
00:24:43,520 --> 00:24:44,600
I grew up in Beijing.

909
00:24:44,840 --> 00:24:46,120
Where do you live now?

910
00:24:46,120 --> 00:24:46,800
(A true Dongcheng local)
Dongcheng.

911
00:24:46,800 --> 00:24:47,480
So you're a Beijing local.

912
00:24:48,120 --> 00:24:49,360
Wait, you don't live in Beijing?

913
00:24:49,360 --> 00:24:50,960
(Growing a bit distant now)
I do. I've always been in Beijing.

914
00:24:50,960 --> 00:24:52,200
You live in Beijing?

915
00:24:52,200 --> 00:24:53,600
Our company is based in Beijing.

916
00:24:54,200 --> 00:24:55,360
Your company is in Beijing?

917
00:24:55,360 --> 00:24:56,840
Isn't it in Chongqing?

918
00:24:56,840 --> 00:24:57,920
Time Fengjun.

919
00:24:57,920 --> 00:24:59,640
It's in Beijing, our HQ.

920
00:24:59,640 --> 00:25:00,640
The HQ is in Beijing.

921
00:25:00,640 --> 00:25:01,040
Wait.

922
00:25:01,040 --> 00:25:02,680
(Curious)
Is your boss named Li Fei?

923
00:25:03,160 --> 00:25:03,560
Yep.

924
00:25:04,040 --> 00:25:05,460
(Core memory unlocked)
I'm Li Fei.

925
00:25:06,680 --> 00:25:07,280
For real?

926
00:25:07,800 --> 00:25:08,400
Yeah.

927
00:25:09,040 --> 00:25:10,480
You guys have done
this dance before, right?

928
00:25:10,920 --> 00:25:11,920
Yeah, we did it together.

929
00:25:12,200 --> 00:25:13,280
They did a dance challenge to this song.

930
00:25:13,280 --> 00:25:15,200
♪I'm Li Fei, no backbone♪

931
00:25:15,200 --> 00:25:16,960
♪Unmoved by gain or loss, joy or sorrow♪

932
00:25:16,960 --> 00:25:17,720
So is it you?

933
00:25:20,720 --> 00:25:22,680
Do you guys live in a dorm?

934
00:25:23,080 --> 00:25:24,480
Yeah, we live together.

935
00:25:24,480 --> 00:25:25,760
Are you still living there now?

936
00:25:25,760 --> 00:25:26,560
Yeah, pretty much.

937
00:25:27,040 --> 00:25:28,920
It's basically like a whole building,

938
00:25:28,920 --> 00:25:30,280
and everyone just lives
in that same building.

939
00:25:31,060 --> 00:25:31,980
(I see)

940
00:25:32,160 --> 00:25:35,080
We used to live in a house together too.

941
00:25:35,400 --> 00:25:36,360
I know.

942
00:25:36,800 --> 00:25:37,720
Six people together.

943
00:25:37,840 --> 00:25:39,640
(Listening intently)
It was like a villa,

944
00:25:39,640 --> 00:25:40,960
and everyone had their own house.

945
00:25:40,960 --> 00:25:41,440
I mean, room.

946
00:25:41,840 --> 00:25:43,880
But the bathrooms and everything
were completely shared.

947
00:25:44,040 --> 00:25:44,960
That's how we started out too.

948
00:25:45,640 --> 00:25:47,120
Seven of us lived in a villa together.

949
00:25:47,600 --> 00:25:48,920
Shared bathrooms?

950
00:25:49,080 --> 00:25:49,600
Yeah.

951
00:25:50,720 --> 00:25:52,280
So every time we

952
00:25:52,280 --> 00:25:54,280
got back after work,
we had to line up to shower.

953
00:25:55,000 --> 00:25:56,840
So you guys have to live together

954
00:25:56,840 --> 00:25:58,200
(Curious)
while the group is active?

955
00:25:58,200 --> 00:25:59,500
(Always together)
Yeah, for two years.

956
00:25:59,680 --> 00:26:01,160
(In the loop)
They're a two-year limited group.

957
00:26:01,640 --> 00:26:02,440
A limited group.

958
00:26:04,820 --> 00:26:37,860
=The Truth S4=
(Viewing Calendar: Restored Version)

959
00:27:09,610 --> 00:27:13,610
♪Come now, players all,
let the game of reason start♪

960
00:27:13,610 --> 00:27:18,050
♪Unlock each hidden trial,
let courage spark the dark♪

961
00:27:20,070 --> 00:27:24,230
♪Night falls slow, shadows grow,
the sleuth is lost inside the maze♪

962
00:27:24,230 --> 00:27:28,450
♪Figures pass, lanterns sparse,
dark currents drift without a trace♪

963
00:27:28,450 --> 00:27:32,220
♪Wind picks up, footsteps rush,
cold laughter swallowed by the dark♪

964
00:27:32,220 --> 00:27:36,330
♪Truth concealed, the night
stands still, and nothing leaves a mark♪

965
00:27:36,510 --> 00:27:40,630
♪An unsigned letter, coded words,
the solvers gather one by one♪

966
00:27:40,630 --> 00:27:44,740
♪A broken game, illusion reigns,
who's hiding what they've done?♪

967
00:27:44,740 --> 00:27:48,380
♪Hushed voices, nerves on edge,
wrapped in smoke and mirrors still♪

968
00:27:48,380 --> 00:27:50,510
♪The next second, deeper riddles,
or the answer to the kill♪

969
00:27:50,510 --> 00:27:54,460
♪Every piece of truth
has finally come to light♪

970
00:27:54,700 --> 00:27:58,620
♪Unlock the mystery, turn the question,
let's begin tonight♪

971
00:27:58,830 --> 00:28:02,980
♪Side by side, no holding back,
follow every clue to find the truth♪

972
00:28:02,980 --> 00:28:06,540
♪The story blurs like flowers in fog,
